IMPORTANT NOTES REGARDING DATASETS:

1. This license applies ONLY to the source code in this repository.

2. The datasets used in this project have separate licenses and access restrictions:

   a) TORGO Dataset:
      - Contact: University of Toronto (complingweb@cs.toronto.edu)
      - Citation: Rudzicz, F., Namasivayam, A. K., & Wolff, T. (2012). 
        The TORGO database of acoustic and articulatory speech from 
        speakers with dysarthria. Language Resources and Evaluation, 
        46(4), 523-541.
      - Restrictions: Research use only, no redistribution

   b) EasyCall Dataset:
      - Contact: Italian Institute of Technology (leonardo.badino@iit.it)
      - Citation: Turrisi, R., Braccia, A., Emanuele, M., Giulietti, S., 
        Fadiga, L., Sensi, M., & Badino, L. (2021). EasyCall corpus: 
        a dysarthric speech dataset for phone call applications.
      - Restrictions: Research use only, no redistribution

3. Users of this code must:
   - Obtain independent access to TORGO and EasyCall datasets
   - Comply with all terms and conditions of dataset providers
   - Not redistribute any dataset files
   - Properly cite both datasets in any publications

4. The OpenAI Whisper model has its own license:
   - Model: MIT License
   - Citation: Radford, A., et al. (2022). Robust Speech Recognition 
     via Large-Scale Weak Supervision. arXiv:2212.04356

5. For academic use:
   - This work is intended for research and educational purposes
   - Commercial use requires verification of all component licenses
   - Consult with your institution's legal department for commercial applications

6. Ethical considerations:
   - This work involves speech data from people with disabilities
   - All use must respect participant privacy and dignity
   - Follow ethical guidelines for assistive technology research

